33. duci: ‘that it be drawn.' In prose the subjunctive, not the infin., is used with hortor (526. iv). arce: the preposition in phrases telling the place where (as also the place to or from which) is more often omitted in poetry than in prose (618. iv). Cf. 1. 8.
